"Block construction & merge benchmark (workload class D). Builds a
large base block, then folds the deep-merge operator `<<` over several
override layers on top of it -- the product's core operation (layering
config defaults with overrides), which had no engine benchmark before
eu-2sa6.6. Both `block` construction and `<<` merge are O(n^2) on
cons-list blocks (ROADMAP section 2), so the base is sized to 3000 keys
to keep the bench in the >1.5s band (~2.5s) rather than the ~5s a
5000-key base would cost. Runs >1.5s on the faster engine."

# One [key, value] element with a computed key.
pa(i): [sym("k{i}"), i]

# One override element for the same key space, offset by a per-layer amount.
pl(off, i): [sym("k{i}"), i + off]

# The 3000-key base block, built once via block/elements.
` :suppress
defaults: block(range(0, 3000) map(pa))

# A 500-key override layer j (overrides keys k0..k499).
mk-layer(j): block(range(0, 500) map(pl((j + 1) * 100000)))

# Fold four override layers onto the base with `<<` (deep-merge).
` :suppress
merged: range(0, 4) map(mk-layer) foldl((<<), defaults)

key-count: merged keys count
value-sum: merged values sum

` { target: :bench-block-merge
    verify: ["default-expectation"] }
bench-block-merge: {
  keys: key-count
  sum: value-sum
  RESULT: if(key-count = 3000,
             if(value-sum = 204498500, :PASS, :FAIL),
             :FAIL)
}
